## Onboarding Timeline Estimate
```
Phase 1: Research & Spec        1–2 weeks
Phase 2: Data Validation        3–5 days
Phase 3: Backtesting            1–2 weeks
Phase 4: Walk-Forward           3–5 days
Phase 5: Implementation         1–2 weeks
Phase 6: Integration Testing    3–5 days
Phase 7: Paper Trading          4–8 weeks
Phase 8: Micro Live             4–6 weeks
Phase 9: Scale-Up               8–12 weeks
───────────────────────────────────────────
Total to full deployment:       ~5–6 months
```

## Gate Failure Protocol
```
If any phase gate fails:

Minor failure (one metric slightly below threshold):
  → Document the gap
  → QR + QD review and address root cause
  → Re-run the failing phase (don't advance)

Major failure (multiple metrics failing, or overfitting detected):
  → Return to Phase 1 — hypothesis may be flawed
  → Do not patch around a fundamentally weak signal

No exceptions for advancing without sign-offs:
  → Phase 7 → 8 requires: QT + Risk Quant
  → Phase 8 → 9 requires: PM + QT + Treasury
```

## Guardrails
- Phases cannot be skipped — every phase catches a different class of failure
- Time minimums are floors, not targets — more time in paper is always better
- Sign-offs must be explicit (written) — verbal approvals are not sufficient for compliance records
- A strategy that fails Phase 3 or 4 must not advance regardless of how promising the hypothesis seems
- The onboarding record (completed checklist) is a compliance document — retain indefinitely
